<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="502" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,259,1042]" pageId="15" pageNumber="502">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,511,537]" pageId="15" pageNumber="502">Description</emphasis>
. General color yellowish to ochraceous. Head and pronotum ochraceous; head with inconspicuous M-line, central frons darker, clypeus and occiput yellowish (
<figureCitation box="[848,954,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1833,1857]" captionTargetBox="[180,1398,205,1787]" captionTargetId="figure-35@14.[154,1433,181,1809]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 11. Male adult holotype of Anacroneuria froehlichi n. sp. A: head and pronotum; B: anterior wing; C: posterior wing; D: sternum IX with hammer; E: penial armature in dorsal view; F: same, ventral view; G: same, lateral view. Scale 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6816787" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6816787/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="502">Fig. 11A</figureCitation>
). Antennae ochraceous, scape with darker spot laterally. Palpi pale yellowish. Pronotum with posterior corners rounded (
<figureCitation box="[1043,1148,583,609]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1833,1857]" captionTargetBox="[180,1398,205,1787]" captionTargetId="figure-35@14.[154,1433,181,1809]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 11. Male adult holotype of Anacroneuria froehlichi n. sp. A: head and pronotum; B: anterior wing; C: posterior wing; D: sternum IX with hammer; E: penial armature in dorsal view; F: same, ventral view; G: same, lateral view. Scale 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6816787" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6816787/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="502">Fig. 11A</figureCitation>
). Wings with membranes ochraceous and conspicuous veins. Presence of 4 to 8 transverse veins between the medial and anterior cubital veins. Legs yellowish with darker stripe in distal part of the femur. Abdomen pale yellowish. Sternum IX with small bristles on posterior margin; hammer as a short truncate cone (
<figureCitation box="[843,945,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1833,1857]" captionTargetBox="[180,1398,205,1787]" captionTargetId="figure-35@14.[154,1433,181,1809]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 11. Male adult holotype of Anacroneuria froehlichi n. sp. A: head and pronotum; B: anterior wing; C: posterior wing; D: sternum IX with hammer; E: penial armature in dorsal view; F: same, ventral view; G: same, lateral view. Scale 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6816787" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6816787/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="502">Fig. 11D</figureCitation>
). Penial armature, in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[1324,1423,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1833,1857]" captionTargetBox="[180,1398,205,1787]" captionTargetId="figure-35@14.[154,1433,181,1809]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 11. Male adult holotype of Anacroneuria froehlichi n. sp. A: head and pronotum; B: anterior wing; C: posterior wing; D: sternum IX with hammer; E: penial armature in dorsal view; F: same, ventral view; G: same, lateral view. Scale 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6816787" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6816787/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="502">Fig. 11E</figureCitation>
), tapering gradually up to the level of distal part of the hooks where there is a rounded expansion, which subsequently narrows sharply in an elongated final process; in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[857,954,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1833,1857]" captionTargetBox="[180,1398,205,1787]" captionTargetId="figure-35@14.[154,1433,181,1809]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 11. Male adult holotype of Anacroneuria froehlichi n. sp. A: head and pronotum; B: anterior wing; C: posterior wing; D: sternum IX with hammer; E: penial armature in dorsal view; F: same, ventral view; G: same, lateral view. Scale 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6816787" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6816787/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="502">Fig. 11F</figureCitation>
), with pair of large distal vesicles and with hooks regularly curved with tips pointed; in the lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[852,955,799,825]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1833,1857]" captionTargetBox="[180,1398,205,1787]" captionTargetId="figure-35@14.[154,1433,181,1809]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 11. Male adult holotype of Anacroneuria froehlichi n. sp. A: head and pronotum; B: anterior wing; C: posterior wing; D: sternum IX with hammer; E: penial armature in dorsal view; F: same, ventral view; G: same, lateral view. Scale 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6816787" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6816787/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="502">Fig. 11G</figureCitation>
), with the apex slightly inclined ventrally. Cerci ochraceous.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="502" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,259,1042]" pageId="15" pageNumber="502">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,871,897]" pageId="15" pageNumber="502">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Miguel &amp; Almeida &amp; Novaes &amp; Bispo" authorityYear="2022" box="[325,598,871,897]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Anacroneuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="502" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="froehlichi">
<emphasis box="[325,598,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="502">Anacroneuria froehlichi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was collected in the streams of Chapada dos Veadeiros, northern 
<collectingRegion country="Brazil" name="Goias" pageId="15" pageNumber="502">Goiás state</collectingRegion>
. This species has a color pattern common to several species of the genus. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Miguel &amp; Almeida &amp; Novaes &amp; Bispo" authorityYear="2022" box="[1033,1172,907,933]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Anacroneuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="502" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="froehlichi">
<emphasis box="[1033,1172,907,933]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="502">A. froehlichi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has penial armature (in dorsal view) with an abruptly narrowed apex, forming a slender process. This penial armature shape of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Miguel &amp; Almeida &amp; Novaes &amp; Bispo" authorityYear="2022" box="[1298,1436,943,969]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Anacroneuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="502" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="froehlichi">
<emphasis box="[1298,1436,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="502">A. froehlichi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is unique, easily distinguishing it from other species of the genus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1428,1015,1042]" pageId="15" pageNumber="502" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,259,1042]" box="[199,1428,1015,1042]" pageId="15" pageNumber="502">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1015,1041]" pageId="15" pageNumber="502">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name honors Claudio Gilberto Froehlich, a pioneer in 
<taxonomicName box="[999,1117,1015,1041]" class="Insecta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="502" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Plecoptera</taxonomicName>
research in South America.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
